<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=299&amp;p=1952#p1952"><![CDATA[
It doesn't look like there are any metal edge connectors in the middle of the connector. You might have to end up glueing a piece of metal there.<br /><br />The one you'd solder to on the famicom side are pretty obvious.<br />See the 2 pins that have no traces that go anywhere? (its on the side with all the parts on it). The unused pin twords the transistors/caps/resistors.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45">drk421</a> — Tue Apr 26, 2005 9:56 pm</p><hr />
